metadata.name: Eyes Into Darkness - Daily
metadata.description:
**Darkness** gives way to oneself, restoring importance to a **few simple essentials**.   

In a suspension of space, where time is marked by biological rhythm. It brings us back to contact with ourselves and to internal dialogue.   

A dialogue that cyclically returns, when we least expect it, even when we do not call it.   

In the essentiality of this visual creation, **everyone finds their own space, their own time, their own evocation**.
